==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whiles
<hw>Whiles</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[See <er>While</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, and <er>-wards</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Meanwhile;
meantime.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The good knight <qex>whiles</qex> humming to himself the lay of
some majored troubadour.</q> <rj><qau>Sir. W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>sometimes; at times.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The whiles</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>While</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whiles</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whiles
<hw>Whiles</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <def>During the time that;
while.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.
Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Agree with thine adversary quickly, <qex>whiles</qex> thou art in
the way with him.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. v. 25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whilk</ent>⟦br⟧
